#8004
At the Temple Altar~
   You stand before the temple altar. Carved from a solid block of black
marble, it is an exquisite example of dwarven craftsmanship. Black pillars
of the same marble hold up the ceiling of this open-aired pavilion, and to
the south a narrow aisle runs its way between hard oaken pews. There is a
small hand painted sign posted as well.
