#8165
the Kir Drax'in Lodge Vestibule~
   The gigantic oak and wrought iron doors were crafted by ancient dwarves,
these doors are a prize posession of the owner of the lodge.  He personally
refinished them and brought them back to life, after salvaging them from the
ruins of a dwarven mountain stronghold.  The walls of the lodge are mostly
four to three foot square stone blocks.  There is a roof over your head but
there are no walls here, just two enormous pillars at each corner to bare the
weight of it.  The floor of the vestibule is polished oak similiar to the
door.
~
80 4 0 0 0 1
