#8166
Kir Drax'in Lodge's Stables~
   Looking north you see a half-door on a spring that is easily swung either
in or out.  To the south of room are the horse stables, where the smell of
fresh horse manure is coming from.  The floor is lined with hay and the barn
is constructed from heavy one foot by one foot solid beams and reclaimed wood
from a nearby windmill.  Looking upward you see high ceilings with ventilation
piped in and down to the woodburning stove that sits on a stone platform near
the stablehand's workbench and shoeing tools.  At the top of the southern
corner of the building you can see a hayloft, which is strangely dark
considering how well lit the rest of the barn is.  Two beady little eyes about
the size of a small child keep catching your attention randomly.
~
