#8170
the Kir Drax'in Lodge Main Lobby~
   This is the busiest room in the lodge at peak hours, except maybe the bar
which is quite busy to your south.  There is a large ornate oaken counter
here, finished at the top by a slab of black marble with specks of volcanic
rock and gold flake.  The floors surrounding the counter are hidden underneath
an imported rug made from a silk and wool blend.  There is a gigantic
fireplace at the north wall surrounded by more reclaimed stone from the old
inn.  There are chairs and couches surrounding the fireplace.  Additionally,
there is a low-rise table with refreshments for the guests of the Kir
Drax'in Lodge.
~
