bar~
   The bar, in all its glory, looks almost alive.  It is crafted from a single
giant base of an enormous oak tree.  The tree must have been 12' in diameter.
Its been hand carved by Finn Elkheart himself.  The embossed carvings tell a
story of the long and colorful history of Kir Drax'in and its people.  The
counter is a single gigantic slab of marble, mostly green with specs of gold
flake and onyx throughout.  Behind the bar are various cups, mugs, and
glasses.  To the back wall shelves upon shelves of liquor and wine.  There are
a few wooden kegs with the house brew.
~
S
#8172
Behind the Bar~
   Oaken and ornate, the shelves reach ten ft high and span the three walls
behind the bar.  Each shelf has an array of imported and domestic liquors.
There are kegs underneath the bar surrounded by large ice blocks, which do not
seem to be melting.  There is a coin safe in the floor where Finn drops his
profits.
~
