#8176
the Hall of the Four Horsemen~
   You are in the hallway that serves entry into two of the four suites in
this wing.  Nobody in there right mind would pick one of the suites to sleep
in.  The air is stale and smells of whiskey and unwashed travellers.  The
walls are stone and dripping with condensation.  Carpet is sopping wet and
moldy.  It is cold, wet, and just right if your already dead.  Perhaps, these
rooms are not for a stable minded individual.  The only light is seeping in
from underneat the doors and from the stairwell to the north.  The hallway
continues southward.
~
