#8179
the Hall of Dragons~
   You find yourself in a hallway with minimal lighting.  The only light
sources are the ornate yet subtle amber lanterns affixed to a cast iron mount
above each door.  The entrances to the rooms are all quite unique from one
another.  Each door has its own style of carvings, moldings, and wood stains.
They covered the floors in carpet fit for kings bare feet, imported from the
far southern city of Xixieqian The walls are solid stone blocks adorned with
framed artwork depicting the dragons of the land.
~
